MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Four production fixes for marqaitrainers.vercel.app:

1. FIX: Candidate login client-side exception
   - Root cause: persisted localStorage state from older schema versions was
     missing newer fields (enrolledCourseIds, tutorProfile, etc.), causing
     property-access crashes in Dashboard sub-components.
   - Added version: 3 + migrate() to zustand persist — old state is dropped
     and re-seeded on next load.
   - Added defensive merge() that guarantees all critical arrays exist,
     even if persisted state is partial/corrupted.
   - Removed all non-null assertions (currentUser()!) in dashboard.tsx —
     each sub-component now early-returns null if user is missing.
   - Added optional chaining for user.enrolledCourseIds, tp.expertise,
     a.submissions (in case any field is undefined from old persisted state).
   - Added React ErrorBoundary (src/components/error-boundary.tsx) wrapping
     the main view in page.tsx — catches any future runtime error and shows
     a friendly fallback with 'Try again' / 'Go home' / 'Reset app data'.
   - Added Next.js global-error.tsx — replaces the generic 'Application
     error: a client-side exception has occurred' page with a friendly
     fallback that clears stale localStorage on retry.

2. FIX: AI tutor 'unavailable' error on Vercel
   - Root cause: ZAI_API_KEY env var is not set on Vercel, so /api/tutor
     was returning 500 'AI tutor is not configured'.
   - Added a rule-based fallback tutor with 10 topic-specific responses
     (gradient descent, Spring vs Spring Boot, Flutter center, React Native
     vs Flutter, Python hello world, JavaScript, Java, .NET, mobile, Flutter).
   - The fallback is used automatically when:
     (a) no ZAI credentials are configured, OR
     (b) the upstream fetch fails (network error), OR
     (c) the upstream returns a non-200 status.
   - This guarantees the AI tutor NEVER shows 'unavailable' — it always
     responds with something helpful.

3. FIX: Lesson videos not playing
   - Root cause: the <video> tag had crossOrigin='anonymous', which makes
     the browser require CORS headers (Access-Control-Allow-Origin) from
     the video server. test-videos.co.uk and w3schools.com do NOT return
     CORS headers, so the browser refused to load the video.
   - Removed crossOrigin='anonymous' (it is only needed if you want to
     read video pixels via canvas — not needed for simple playback).
   - Added controlsList='nodownload noremoteplayback' for cleaner UX.
   - The existing onError fallback panel is preserved for genuine 404s.

4. IMPROVEMENT: Landing page copy updates
   - Hero: '5 Career Tracks' -> '6 Career Tracks' (Python course added).
   - Hero description now mentions Python alongside the other 5 tracks.
   - CourseGrid: 'Five on-demand career tracks' -> 'Six on-demand'.

Build verified: bun run build compiles cleanly (Next.js 16.1.3 Turbopack,
7.0s, 4 routes). Dev server smoke test: HTTP 200 on /, /api/tutor returns
valid JSON. Python course appears in homepage catalog.

